1
00:00:29,797 --> 00:00:32,004
CAPRICORN ONE

2
00:01:18,934 --> 00:01:21,645
<i>Good morning, ladies and</i>
<i>gentlemen. This is Paul Cunningham,</i>

3
00:01:21,682 --> 00:01:22,860
<i>Capricorn Control.</i>

4
00:01:22,897 --> 00:01:26,231
<i>The time is three minutes after six,</i>
<i>Eastern Daylight Time.</i>

5
00:01:26,609 --> 00:01:31,022
<i>Were coming up on</i>
<i>T-minus 32 minutes. 21 seconds... mark.</i>

6
00:01:31,489 --> 00:01:34,868
<i>To facilitate the broadcast media,</i>
<i>we will precede each announcement</i>

7
00:01:34,905 --> 00:01:38,252
<i>with a 5 seconds. tone, followed</i>
<i>by a 1 second pause.</i>

8
00:01:38,289 --> 00:01:42,702
<i>Anyone who hasn't got a press kit</i>
<i>can pick one at the information trailer.</i>

9
00:01:42,835 --> 00:01:45,213
<i>At the present time,</i>
<i>all systems are go,</i>

10
00:01:45,249 --> 00:01:46,928
<i>all lights are green.</i>

11
00:01:46,965 --> 00:01:50,761
<i>To review the morning for you,</i>
<i>at T-minus 8 hours, 5 minutes.</i>

12
00:01:50,797 --> 00:01:52,893
<i>Launch Complex thirty-nine</i>
<i>was cleared</i>

13
00:01:52,930 --> 00:01:55,849
<i>and we began to load liquid</i>
<i>propellant into the launch vehicle.</i>

14
00:01:55,886 --> 00:01:57,940
<i>At T-minus 4 hours, 30 minutes.</i>

15
00:01:57,977 --> 00:02:00,443
<i>Colonel Charles Brubaker,</i>
<i>the Command Pilot,</i>

16
00:02:00,479 --> 00:02:03,752
<i>Lieutenant Colonel Peter Willis</i>
<i>and Commander John Walker</i>

17
00:02:03,788 --> 00:02:07,025
<i>were awakened by Dr. Roger</i>
<i>Burroughs, the flight surgeon.</i>

18
00:02:07,279 --> 00:02:11,324
<i>They were given a final physical</i>
<i>examination and pronounced all fit.</i>

19
00:02:11,533 --> 00:02:14,828
<i>The crew then had a breakfast</i>
<i>consisting of half a grapefruit,</i>

20
00:02:14,865 --> 00:02:16,460
<i>a ten ounce steak,</i>

21
00:02:16,497 --> 00:02:19,831
<i>twelve ounces of orange juice,</i>
<i>two eggs and toast.</i>

22
00:02:20,251 --> 00:02:22,467
<i>The crew is now in the gantry</i>
<i>access arm,</i>

23
00:02:22,504 --> 00:02:25,215
<i>where they're preparing to enter</i>
<i>the spacecraft.</i>

24
00:02:25,251 --> 00:02:27,300
<i>We're at T-minus 30 minutes.</i>
<i>and counting.</i>

25
00:02:27,337 --> 00:02:28,878
<i>This is Capricorn Control.</i>

26
00:02:29,136 --> 00:02:31,342
- Good morning, gentlemen.
- Good morning, Horace.

27
00:02:31,680 --> 00:02:32,895
Are we late?

28
00:02:32,932 --> 00:02:34,522
Traffic was terrible.

29
00:02:34,558 --> 00:02:36,482
Well, I see you're all in good spirits.

30
00:02:36,519 --> 00:02:39,520
- Have you done the EDS test yet?
- They're almost completed.

31
00:02:44,778 --> 00:02:46,818
- Do you want us to enter?
- In a moment.

32
00:02:47,114 --> 00:02:48,120
What's up?

33
00:02:48,157 --> 00:02:50,414
I'm not very good at things like this.

34
00:02:50,451 --> 00:02:53,238
I've known you, especially
Colonel Brubaker,

35
00:02:54,163 --> 00:02:55,194
for some time.

36
00:02:56,916 --> 00:02:59,870
What you're about to do today,
I've spent my life.

37
00:03:01,505 --> 00:03:05,550
I'd just like yuh to know that I feel
that all I've ever worked for,

38
00:03:06,260 --> 00:03:08,466
it has meaning today,
and I'm very proud.

39
00:03:08,929 --> 00:03:10,305
Proud of the program

40
00:03:10,931 --> 00:03:13,933
and proud of what I've been able to
contribute in some small way, and

41
00:03:15,061 --> 00:03:16,306
proud of you.

42
00:03:17,772 --> 00:03:20,066
I'd like for you to take
this Bible with you,

43
00:03:20,103 --> 00:03:22,032
from me, from all of us.

44
00:03:22,069 --> 00:03:24,358
Why, Horace, I don't know
what to say.

45
00:03:24,947 --> 00:03:27,520
- Well, try saying nothing for a change.
- Horace...

46
00:03:28,909 --> 00:03:29,823
thank you.

47
00:03:30,995 --> 00:03:32,620
We'd be honored to take this with us.

48
00:03:34,290 --> 00:03:36,117
Well, gentlemen, let's go to Mars.

49
00:03:37,210 --> 00:03:39,692
<i>This is Paul Cunningham,</i>
<i>Capricorn Control.</i>

50
00:03:39,729 --> 00:03:42,137
<i>We're now at T-minus 21 minutes.</i>
<i>and counting.</i>

51
00:03:42,174 --> 00:03:45,302
<i>Wives of the flight crew at the Cape</i>
<i>will be flown back to Houston</i>

52
00:03:45,339 --> 00:03:47,560
<i>- following launch.</i>
- Good morning, Congressman Peaker.

53
00:03:47,597 --> 00:03:50,767
We've reserved three of the best seats
for you and for General Enders,

54
00:03:50,803 --> 00:03:52,012
right next to Vice President.

55
00:03:52,310 --> 00:03:53,233
Is he here yet?

56
00:03:53,269 --> 00:03:55,013
No, sir, he's due any moment.

57
00:03:56,857 --> 00:03:59,811
Asshole probably thinks they'll delay
the launch for him.

58
00:04:00,277 --> 00:04:02,801
Someone should tell him this is not
a bridge opening.

59
00:04:02,837 --> 00:04:05,288
I hope you and Mrs. Peaker will be
very comfortable.

60
00:04:05,324 --> 00:04:08,328
The Agency would like you to have
these commemorative binoculars

61
00:04:08,364 --> 00:04:10,783
to help you watch the launch
and to remember this day.

62
00:04:11,831 --> 00:04:13,623
That's very nice. Look, Emily.

63
00:04:14,167 --> 00:04:16,712
They have the date,
Capricorn One emblem in gold.

64
00:04:16,748 --> 00:04:19,003
- Very nice, Hollis.
- I'm glad you like them.

65
00:04:19,039 --> 00:04:21,258
Well, we'll need another pair
for my wife.

66
00:04:21,295 --> 00:04:22,432
I, I beg your pardon, sir?

67
00:04:22,468 --> 00:04:24,510
Oh, don't make a fuss, Hollis,
it's all right.

68
00:04:24,546 --> 00:04:26,552
I said, 'we'll need another pair
for my wife.'

69
00:04:27,098 --> 00:04:29,559
- It's really not necessary.
- Here, Emily, take mine.

70
00:04:29,596 --> 00:04:31,412
- I really won't need them.
- No, I don't...

71
00:04:31,449 --> 00:04:33,193
Congressman Peaker,
there's only a limited...

72
00:04:33,230 --> 00:04:36,599
I didn't quite hear what you said.
Would you mind repeating it, please?

73
00:04:37,318 --> 00:04:40,354
Oh, there's no problem.
I'll get another pair right away.

74
00:04:40,863 --> 00:04:42,274
Very thoughtful of you.

75
00:04:43,866 --> 00:04:47,579
<i>This is Capricorn Control. We are at</i>
<i>T-minus 15 minutes. and counting.</i>

76
00:04:47,615 --> 00:04:50,003
<i>All systems are go.</i>
<i>All lights are green.</i>

77
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:53,841
<i>Mission Control has reported the</i>
<i>spacecraft is now on external power.</i>

78
00:04:53,877 --> 00:04:57,792
<i>The launch vehicle will transfer to</i>
<i>full internal power at T-minus 50 seconds.</i>

79
00:04:58,257 --> 00:05:00,384
<i>Both Ascension and Canary</i>
<i>tracking stations</i>

80
00:05:00,421 --> 00:05:02,058
<i>report clear reception.</i>

81
00:05:02,095 --> 00:05:04,811
<i>The prime recovery ship,</i>
<i>in the event of a terminated flight,</i>

82
00:05:04,848 --> 00:05:08,643
<i>will be the U.S.S. Kitty Hawk, which</i>
<i>is located 350 nautical miles</i>

83
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:11,810
<i>South, Southeast of Bermuda.</i>
<i>This is Capricorn Control.</i>

84
00:05:22,117 --> 00:05:23,908
- Hello, Emily.
- How are you?

85
00:05:24,160 --> 00:05:25,250
- Phyllis?
- Hello, Hollis.

86
00:05:25,287 --> 00:05:28,373
Emily, glad to see you.
Hollis, how are you?

87
00:05:28,410 --> 00:05:30,117
Very well, Mr. Vice President.

88
00:05:30,960 --> 00:05:34,635
- How is the President today?
- Oh, just fine, thank you, Hollis.

89
00:05:34,672 --> 00:05:38,676
He asked me to personally express
his regrets at being unable to be here.

90
00:05:38,713 --> 00:05:41,184
There were some pressing matters

91
00:05:41,221 --> 00:05:43,223
that needed his attention
in Washington.

92
00:05:43,259 --> 00:05:44,598
Like getting re-elected?

93
00:05:44,933 --> 00:05:48,687
Mr. Vice President? I hope you and
Mrs. Price will be very comfortable.

94
00:05:48,724 --> 00:05:51,691
The Agency would like you to have
these commemorative binoculars

95
00:05:51,727 --> 00:05:54,152
to help you watch the launch
and to remember this day.

96
00:05:54,188 --> 00:05:55,950
- Thank you.
- Thank you, very much.

97
00:05:55,987 --> 00:05:57,947
- They're very nice.
- What is your name, son?

98
00:05:57,984 --> 00:05:59,276
Hughes, sir. Mark Hughes.

99
00:05:59,950 --> 00:06:01,029
You learn pretty quick.

100
00:06:01,326 --> 00:06:03,034
- You'll do all right.
- Thank you, sir.

101
00:06:04,997 --> 00:06:07,036
<i>We're at T-minus 10 minutes.</i>
<i>and counting.</i>

102
00:06:07,416 --> 00:06:08,447
<i>Stage one is green.</i>

103
00:06:08,751 --> 00:06:10,079
<i>Stage two is green.</i>

104
00:06:10,586 --> 00:06:12,051
<i>Stage two is green.</i>

105
00:06:12,088 --> 00:06:14,924
<i>Malfunction Detect System,</i>
<i>on second panel.</i>

106
00:06:14,961 --> 00:06:17,250
<i>Roger. M.D.S. on second panel.</i>

107
00:06:17,552 --> 00:06:21,633
<i>Capricorn One, we confirm T.A.R. S</i>
<i>and M.D.S. You are green on both.</i>

108
00:06:23,767 --> 00:06:26,520
<i>You are go for Inertial Guidance</i>
<i>and O.A.M.S. checks.</i>

109
00:06:26,557 --> 00:06:27,765
<i>Roger, Houston.</i>

110
00:06:28,022 --> 00:06:30,613
Gentlemen, we're ready
to close the hatch.

111
00:06:30,650 --> 00:06:33,188
<i>Anybody wanna get out,</i>
<i>this is your last chance.</i>

112
00:06:33,361 --> 00:06:36,740
<i>Hey, Horace, is Mars the red one</i>
<i>or the green one? I forgot.</i>

113
00:06:36,776 --> 00:06:40,077
Twenty-four billion dollars to put
crazy people into space.

114
00:06:40,113 --> 00:06:41,488
<i>Keeps us off the streets.</i>

115
00:06:45,041 --> 00:06:48,291
<i>Colonel Brubaker has reaffirmed</i>
<i>the completion of the EDS checks.</i>

116
00:06:48,961 --> 00:06:51,172
<i>Mission Control reports</i>
<i>all systems are go,</i>

117
00:06:51,209 --> 00:06:52,548
<i>all lights are green.</i>

118
00:06:52,841 --> 00:06:55,510
<i>James Kelloway, Director of the</i>
<i>Manned Space Program,</i>

119
00:06:55,547 --> 00:06:57,184
<i>is in Houston at this moment.</i>

120
00:06:57,221 --> 00:06:59,926
<i>He is in full voice contact</i>
<i>with the flight crew.</i>

121
00:07:01,475 --> 00:07:03,515
<i>Landing Module O.I. shutdown.</i>

122
00:07:03,811 --> 00:07:05,934
<i>O.I., shutdown complete.</i>

123
00:07:06,397 --> 00:07:09,398
<i>Capricorn One, you should have</i>
<i>full C.M. internal power.</i>

124
00:07:10,151 --> 00:07:12,228
<i>Roger, Houston.</i>
<i>We have internal power.</i>

125
00:07:12,404 --> 00:07:14,278
<i>Vehicle final status check.</i>

126
00:07:14,865 --> 00:07:16,580
<i>Begin status check.</i>

127
00:07:16,617 --> 00:07:21,160
<i>- T.L.R. pressure reading is 45.2</i>
<i>- Roger, Houston.</i>

128
00:07:21,580 --> 00:07:23,490
<i>Roger, Capricorn, we copy.</i>

129
00:07:23,750 --> 00:07:26,371
Bru, would you and your men,
please, follow me?

130
00:07:26,628 --> 00:07:27,843
Hey, what the hell is this?

131
00:07:27,879 --> 00:07:30,090
There's no time to explain.
Please, follow me.

132
00:07:30,126 --> 00:07:31,096
Are you nuts?

133
00:07:31,133 --> 00:07:33,677
I said there's no time to explain!
This is an emergency!

134
00:07:33,714 --> 00:07:35,006
Please, follow me, now!

135
00:07:43,354 --> 00:07:45,320
<i>This is Paul Cunningham,</i>
<i>Capricorn Control.</i>

136
00:07:45,356 --> 00:07:47,614
<i>The space vehicle final checks</i>
<i>have been completed</i>

137
00:07:47,651 --> 00:07:50,404
<i>and the access arm is swinging</i>
<i>into a final retract position.</i>

138
00:07:50,440 --> 00:07:52,912
<i>The destruct systems</i>
<i>are now fully armed.</i>

139
00:07:52,948 --> 00:07:57,943
- T.L.R. pressure reading is 45.2.
<i>- Roger, Houston, 45.2.</i>

140
00:07:58,412 --> 00:08:02,078
<i>The flight crew has completed the</i>
<i>launch vehicle range safety checks.</i>

141
00:08:02,375 --> 00:08:06,296
<i>T-minus 50 seconds. the launch vehicle</i>
<i>will be on full internal power,</i>

142
00:08:06,333 --> 00:08:08,971
<i>that begins the actual</i>
<i>launch sequence.</i>

143
00:08:09,007 --> 00:08:12,590
<i>The weather is reported good.</i>
<i>Scattered clouds at 10.000 feet.</i>

144
00:08:13,596 --> 00:08:16,050
<i>All systems are go.</i>
<i>All lights are green.</i>

145
00:08:16,087 --> 00:08:18,506
<i>We're at T-minus 3 minutes. 6 seconds.,</i>
<i>mark.</i>

146
00:08:19,143 --> 00:08:23,148
<i>An officer has given a go to begin</i>
<i>the firing automatic sequence.</i>

147
00:08:23,184 --> 00:08:26,526
<i>From now until T-minus 50 seconds,</i>
<i>that system is pre-set.</i>

148
00:08:26,563 --> 00:08:29,201
Initial stage thruster check is normal.

149
00:08:29,238 --> 00:08:32,192
<i>We're coming up on</i>
<i>T-minus 1 min. 30 seconds.</i>

150
00:08:32,324 --> 00:08:34,660
<i>The final range safety checks</i>
<i>are completed.</i>

151
00:08:34,697 --> 00:08:36,996
<i>The Launch Safety Officer</i>
<i>reports all systems</i>

152
00:08:37,033 --> 00:08:39,369
<i>are normal and we are Go</i>
<i>at this time.</i>

153
00:08:39,499 --> 00:08:41,871
<i>The launch escape tower is now</i>
<i>fully armed.</i>

154
00:08:42,043 --> 00:08:43,342
<i>In the event of an abort,</i>

155
00:08:43,378 --> 00:08:46,799
<i>the tower will carry the command</i>
<i>module away from the launch vehicle</i>

156
00:08:46,835 --> 00:08:50,049
<i>and will activate a system of</i>
<i>control shift at 10.000 feet.</i>

157
00:08:50,469 --> 00:08:53,723
<i>The flight crew reports all guidance</i>
<i>and navigation systems</i>

158
00:08:53,759 --> 00:08:54,838
<i>functioning properly.</i>

159
00:08:54,933 --> 00:08:58,853
<i>The Range Safety Officer reports</i>
<i>alternating systems are operating.</i>

160
00:08:58,890 --> 00:09:00,514
<i>This is Capricorn Control.</i>

161
00:09:06,987 --> 00:09:09,443
It's that big tall white thing over there.

162
00:09:10,491 --> 00:09:11,570
You can't miss it.

163
00:09:16,498 --> 00:09:18,813
<i>This is Paul Cunningham,</i>
<i>Capricorn Control.</i>

164
00:09:18,849 --> 00:09:21,260
<i>We're at T-minus 1 min.</i>
<i>and still counting.</i>

165
00:09:21,297 --> 00:09:23,636
<i>All systems are go.</i>
<i>All lights are green.</i>

166
00:09:23,672 --> 00:09:26,923
<i>We should have launch vehicle</i>
<i>power transfer right about now.</i>

167
00:09:28,886 --> 00:09:31,723
<i>Roger, Houston, we read</i>
<i>nominal A.L.C.S.</i>

168
00:09:31,759 --> 00:09:32,754
<i>Roger, Captain.</i>

169
00:09:33,725 --> 00:09:35,607
<i>We're at T-minus 30 seconds.</i>

170
00:09:35,644 --> 00:09:38,847
At the present time, all systems
are go. All lights are green.

171
00:09:46,531 --> 00:09:48,455
Gentlemen, we're going to be
a little while.

172
00:09:48,491 --> 00:09:51,029
You and your men might be more
comfortable in these.

173
00:09:56,166 --> 00:09:59,084
<i>We're at T-minus 18 seconds.</i>
<i>from lift-off.</i>

174
00:09:59,962 --> 00:10:01,955
<i>We're T-minus 15 seconds.</i>

175
00:10:05,468 --> 00:10:09,466
<i>T-minus 10 seconds., nine, eight</i>
<i>- we have ignition-</i>

176
00:10:09,806 --> 00:10:12,760
<i>six, five -we have outboard</i>
engines-

177
00:10:12,934 --> 00:10:16,318
<i>three -we have inboard engines-</i>
<i>one, zero.</i>

178
00:10:16,355 --> 00:10:20,187
<i>We have a launch commit. We have</i>
<i>a lift-off at 35 minutes. after the hour.</i>

179
00:10:24,906 --> 00:10:26,400
<i>Roger. We are starting yaw.</i>

180
00:10:27,158 --> 00:10:28,999
<i>Roger, roll program complete.</i>

181
00:10:29,035 --> 00:10:31,288
<i>Vehicles on targets and running</i>
<i>smoothly.</i>

182
00:10:31,324 --> 00:10:32,699
<i>Looking good, Capricorn.</i>

183
00:10:32,915 --> 00:10:35,131
<i>We're coming up on T-plus 40 seconds.</i>

184
00:10:35,167 --> 00:10:37,294
<i>Staging should be in the next</i>
- 30 seconds.

185
00:10:37,331 --> 00:10:39,940
<i>Outboard cutoff should be 10 seconds.</i>

186
00:10:39,976 --> 00:10:42,550
- Obeco, Capricorn.
<i>- Roger, Houston.</i>

187
00:10:42,587 --> 00:10:43,723
<i>Have outboard cutoff.</i>

188
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:47,681
<i>Obeco at T-plus 2 minutes. 29 seconds.</i>
<i>Going for staging.</i>

189
00:10:47,717 --> 00:10:49,223
You are go for staging, Capricorn.

190
00:10:49,641 --> 00:10:51,599
<i>Roger, Houston.</i>
<i>Five,</i>

191
00:10:51,977 --> 00:10:53,886
<i>four, three,</i>

192
00:10:54,396 --> 00:10:56,140
<i>two, one.</i>

193
00:10:57,024 --> 00:10:58,269
<i>We reached staging.</i>

194
00:10:58,484 --> 00:10:59,282
We copy.

195
00:10:59,318 --> 00:11:04,032
<i>We have separation. Confirmed.</i>
<i>T-plus 2 minutes. 43 seconds.</i>

196
00:11:04,068 --> 00:11:06,191
- S-two ignition.
<i>- We have S-two.</i>

197
00:11:06,410 --> 00:11:08,042
<i>We have second stage ignition.</i>

198
00:11:08,078 --> 00:11:10,998
<i>S- two ignition at T-plus</i>
<i>- 2 minutes. 46 seconds.</i>

199
00:11:11,034 --> 00:11:13,548
<i>The vehicle is 47 miles down range.</i>

200
00:11:13,584 --> 00:11:17,250
<i>Altitude: 43 miles.</i>
<i>Velocity: 6.100 miles per hour.</i>

201
00:11:17,630 --> 00:11:21,468
Mr. Vice President, please,
give my regards to the President.

202
00:11:21,504 --> 00:11:23,923
Oh, yes, I'll be very happy
to do that, Hollis.

203
00:11:24,429 --> 00:11:28,017
I, uh, hope that whatever problems
he found so important

204
00:11:28,053 --> 00:11:29,899
not to be here today,

205
00:11:29,935 --> 00:11:31,979
I hope he has considerable success
with them.

206
00:11:32,016 --> 00:11:33,987
Well, that's really very sporting
of you.

207
00:11:34,023 --> 00:11:37,689
I'm sure the President will be very
pleased to learn of your support.

208
00:11:38,194 --> 00:11:41,698
The President would get considerable
more of my humble support

209
00:11:41,735 --> 00:11:45,165
if he would only be a little more
helpful with this program here.

210
00:11:45,202 --> 00:11:49,070
Now, Hollis, you know the President
is most interested in this program.

211
00:11:49,457 --> 00:11:51,699
I am most interested in a lot of things,

212
00:11:52,084 --> 00:11:53,958
including my wife's bridge game.

213
00:11:54,462 --> 00:11:56,419
That is not the same as
supporting something.

214
00:11:57,299 --> 00:12:02,471
Hollis, there are many people who feel
that we have problems here, on Earth

215
00:12:02,507 --> 00:12:03,727
that merit our attention

216
00:12:03,764 --> 00:12:07,098
before we spent billions of dollars
on outer space.

217
00:12:07,393 --> 00:12:10,730
There are a number of people who feel
there are no more pressing problems

218
00:12:10,766 --> 00:12:12,853
than our declining position
in world leadership.

219
00:12:13,483 --> 00:12:15,974
It was wonderful seeing you again,
Hollis.

220
00:12:16,319 --> 00:12:18,727
The pleasure was all mine,
Mr. Vice President.

221
00:12:19,531 --> 00:12:22,123
<i>This is Paul Cunningham,</i>
<i>Capricorn Control.</i>

222
00:12:22,159 --> 00:12:25,326
<i>You're at T-plus 2 hours, 16 minutes,</i>
<i>into the flight.</i>

223
00:12:25,579 --> 00:12:28,020
<i>The spacecraft is now</i>
<i>in elliptical orbit</i>

224
00:12:28,056 --> 00:12:30,460
<i>with an apogee of</i>
<i>- 141 nautical miles</i>

225
00:12:30,496 --> 00:12:33,093
<i>and a perigee of 122 nautical miles.</i>

226
00:12:33,129 --> 00:12:36,508
<i>Mission Control reports full voice</i>
<i>contact with the flight crew.</i>

227
00:12:36,545 --> 00:12:38,252
<i>This is Capricorn Control.</i>

228
00:12:39,052 --> 00:12:41,185
Welcome, Colonel.
Would you please come with us?

229
00:12:41,222 --> 00:12:44,329
I'm not going anywhere till somebody
tells us what the hell's going on.

230
00:12:44,366 --> 00:12:47,799
- Everything will be explained to you.
- Bullshit, I wanna know right now!

231
00:12:47,835 --> 00:12:51,232
Colonel, I know this sounds strange,
we are all working for the same thing.

232
00:12:51,269 --> 00:12:52,395
We are not your enemy.

233
00:13:17,428 --> 00:13:18,673
Please, wait here.

234
00:13:27,105 --> 00:13:29,561
I suppose you're wondering
why I called you up here.

235
00:13:47,210 --> 00:13:47,875
Good morning.

236
00:13:48,211 --> 00:13:50,169
Hi there, Dr. Kelloway,
nice to see you.

237
00:13:51,006 --> 00:13:52,916
A funny thing happened
on the way to Mars.

238
00:13:59,724 --> 00:14:01,384
Well, why don't you all sit down?

239
00:14:03,603 --> 00:14:04,517
Well.

240
00:14:11,487 --> 00:14:12,483
Okay,

241
00:14:13,489 --> 00:14:14,604
here it is.

242
00:14:16,284 --> 00:14:19,487
I have to start by saying that
if there was any other way,

243
00:14:20,789 --> 00:14:25,166
if there was even a slight chance
of another alternative,

244
00:14:25,878 --> 00:14:29,496
I would give anything not to be here
with you now, anything.

245
00:14:31,550 --> 00:14:33,377
Bru, how long have we known
each other?

246
00:14:35,847 --> 00:14:38,516
Sixteen years, that's how long,

247
00:14:39,351 --> 00:14:40,631
sixteen years.

248
00:14:42,646 --> 00:14:44,570
You should have seen yourself then.

249
00:14:44,606 --> 00:14:46,848
You seemed walked out
of a Wheaties box.

250
00:14:47,193 --> 00:14:50,609
And me, all sweaty palmed and
deadly serious.

251
00:14:51,656 --> 00:14:55,744
I told everybody about this dream I had
of conquering the New Frontier

252
00:14:55,780 --> 00:14:58,455
and they all looked at me
like I was nuts.

253
00:14:58,491 --> 00:15:00,115
You looked at me and said, "yes".

254
00:15:00,874 --> 00:15:03,210
I remember when you told me
Kay was pregnant.

255
00:15:03,247 --> 00:15:05,002
We even went out and got crocked.

256
00:15:05,588 --> 00:15:09,091
I remember when Charles was born.
We went out and got crocked again.

257
00:15:09,128 --> 00:15:12,220
The two of us, Captain Terrific
and the Mad Doctor

258
00:15:12,256 --> 00:15:14,144
talking about reaching the stars

259
00:15:14,180 --> 00:15:17,431
and the bartender telling us
maybe we'd had enough.

260
00:15:17,768 --> 00:15:19,013
Sixteen years.

261
00:15:20,270 --> 00:15:22,144
And then, Armstrong,

262
00:15:23,065 --> 00:15:26,897
stepped out on the Moon
and we cried. We were so proud.

263
00:15:28,905 --> 00:15:33,285
Willis, you and Walker, you came in
about then, both bright and talented.

264
00:15:33,321 --> 00:15:35,459
Looked at me in my
wash and wear shirt,

265
00:15:35,495 --> 00:15:38,450
carrying on this hot love affair
with my slide rule

266
00:15:38,791 --> 00:15:41,496
and even you were caught up
in what we'd done.

267
00:15:44,714 --> 00:15:48,297
I remember when Glenn made
his first orbit in Mercury.

268
00:15:49,010 --> 00:15:52,011
They put up television sets in
Grand Central Station,

269
00:15:52,556 --> 00:15:56,506
and tens of thousands of people
missed their trains to watch.

270
00:15:57,937 --> 00:16:00,807
You know, when Apollo Seventeen
landed on the Moon,

271
00:16:01,732 --> 00:16:04,485
people were callin' up the networks
and bitchin'

272
00:16:04,522 --> 00:16:07,238
because reruns of I Love Lucy
were cancelled.

273
00:16:07,275 --> 00:16:08,829
Reruns, for Chrissake!

274
00:16:08,865 --> 00:16:11,097
I can understand if it was
the new Lucy Show.

275
00:16:11,133 --> 00:16:13,328
I mean, what the hell is
a walk on the Moon?

276
00:16:13,365 --> 00:16:14,324
But reruns?

277
00:16:14,747 --> 00:16:15,778
Oh, Jesus!

278
00:16:16,874 --> 00:16:19,085
And then, suddenly,
everybody started talking

279
00:16:19,121 --> 00:16:20,925
about how much everything cost.

280
00:16:20,962 --> 00:16:23,833
Was it really worth twenty billion
to go to another planet?

281
00:16:24,132 --> 00:16:27,093
What about cancer? What about
the slums? How much does it cost?

282
00:16:27,130 --> 00:16:29,716
How much does any dream cost?
For Chrissake!

283
00:16:29,753 --> 00:16:32,302
Since when is there an accountant
for ideas?

284
00:16:34,768 --> 00:16:36,808
You know who was
at the launch today?

285
00:16:37,355 --> 00:16:38,635
Not the President,

286
00:16:39,190 --> 00:16:41,266
the Vice President, that's who.

287
00:16:42,694 --> 00:16:45,066
The Vice President
and his plump wife.

288
00:16:47,407 --> 00:16:48,985
The President was busy.

289
00:16:50,703 --> 00:16:52,078
He's not busy.

290
00:16:52,788 --> 00:16:54,496
he's just a little bit scared.

291
00:16:56,626 --> 00:16:58,007
He sat there two months ago

292
00:16:58,044 --> 00:17:00,998
and put his feet up on Woodrow
Wilson desk.

293
00:17:01,464 --> 00:17:03,089
And he said, "Jim...

294
00:17:04,134 --> 00:17:05,379
make it good.

295
00:17:06,553 --> 00:17:08,593
Congress is on my back.

296
00:17:09,765 --> 00:17:12,476
They're looking for a reason
to cancel the program.

297
00:17:12,513 --> 00:17:14,718
We can't afford another screw-up!

298
00:17:15,938 --> 00:17:18,856
Make it good!
You have my every good wish."

299
00:17:19,609 --> 00:17:23,697
His every good wish. I got his
sanctimonious Vice President,

300
00:17:23,733 --> 00:17:24,978
that's what I got!

301
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:29,783
And so there we are,
after all those hopes

302
00:17:29,954 --> 00:17:31,753
and all that dreaming.

303
00:17:31,789 --> 00:17:36,002
He sits there with those flags
behind his chair

304
00:17:36,039 --> 00:17:38,502
and tells we can't afford
a screw-up.

305
00:17:38,538 --> 00:17:40,929
And guess what?
We had a screw-up.

306
00:17:40,966 --> 00:17:44,798
A first-class, bonafide,
made-in-America screw-up!

307
00:17:45,638 --> 00:17:49,308
The nice people from Con-Amalgamate
delivered a life-support system

308
00:17:49,345 --> 00:17:52,496
cheap enough so they could make
a profit on the deal.

309
00:17:52,533 --> 00:17:55,649
Works out fine for everybody.
Con-Amalgamate makes money,

310
00:17:55,685 --> 00:17:57,859
we have our life-support system,

311
00:17:57,896 --> 00:17:59,104
everything is peachy!

312
00:17:59,403 --> 00:18:02,759
Except they made a little bit
too much profit.

313
00:18:02,796 --> 00:18:06,116
We found out two months ago,
it won't work.

314
00:18:06,827 --> 00:18:10,991
You guys would all be dead in three
weeks. It's as simple as that.

315
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:14,878
So all I have to do is report that
and scrub the mission.

316
00:18:14,914 --> 00:18:16,586
Congress has its excuse,

317
00:18:16,797 --> 00:18:20,213
the President still has his desk
and we have no more program.

318
00:18:20,509 --> 00:18:23,131
What's sixteen years?
An actual drop in the bucket!

319
00:18:25,932 --> 00:18:28,685
All right, that's the end of the speech.
Now, we're getting

320
00:18:28,721 --> 00:18:30,843
to what they call
the moment of the truth.

321
00:18:31,521 --> 00:18:32,600
Come with me,

322
00:18:33,732 --> 00:18:35,143
I wanna show you something.

323
00:18:41,532 --> 00:18:46,241
<i>Roger, Houston. TMI burn time</i>
<i>will be 5 minutes. 45 seconds.</i>

324
00:18:46,538 --> 00:18:47,948
<i>Roger, Capricorn.</i>

325
00:18:50,041 --> 00:18:52,663
Delta vapor burn time 3.3 seconds.

326
00:18:55,005 --> 00:18:58,209
There's a door here. I'm gonna open it
and walk into another area.

327
00:18:58,467 --> 00:19:02,417
If you follow me, you'll see a bit more.
I'll answer some questions and...

328
00:19:03,306 --> 00:19:04,586
and we're going to...

329
00:19:05,850 --> 00:19:07,345
Why don't you just follow me?

330
00:19:29,918 --> 00:19:32,670
You don't really think you're gonna
get away with this?

331
00:19:33,255 --> 00:19:34,999
Well, I don't know, it's a chance.

332
00:19:35,299 --> 00:19:37,625
Maybe it's not a very good one,
but it's a chance.

333
00:19:38,803 --> 00:19:41,888
- Who knows about this?
- Almost nobody.

334
00:19:42,515 --> 00:19:45,137
Houston is monitoring the actual flight.

335
00:19:45,477 --> 00:19:48,647
All the telemetry is coming from
the Command Module,

336
00:19:48,684 --> 00:19:50,529
so are your voices and medical data.

337
00:19:50,566 --> 00:19:53,520
We recorded everything from
the practice simulations.

338
00:19:54,403 --> 00:19:55,518
They don't know.

339
00:19:56,322 --> 00:19:59,951
All we need from you is the actual
television transmissions

340
00:19:59,988 --> 00:20:02,822
during the flight and the Mars landing,
that's all.

341
00:20:03,246 --> 00:20:05,239
Just the television transmissions.

342
00:20:05,624 --> 00:20:06,739
That's all?

343
00:20:07,167 --> 00:20:09,207
Just the television transmissions.

344
00:20:11,130 --> 00:20:13,930
We inserted a change in
the onboard computer,

345
00:20:13,966 --> 00:20:17,095
so the spacecraft will land
two hundred miles off target

346
00:20:17,131 --> 00:20:18,602
when it returns to Earth.

347
00:20:18,638 --> 00:20:21,260
You'll be flown to an island
near that point.

348
00:20:21,641 --> 00:20:23,816
From there you'll be transferred
to a helicopter.

349
00:20:23,852 --> 00:20:28,100
The helicopter will fly you to the space
capsule and you'll be put inside.

350
00:20:29,066 --> 00:20:32,904
It'll take the Recovery Forces
a minimum of an hour and a half

351
00:20:32,940 --> 00:20:34,911
to reach the splashdown site.

352
00:20:34,948 --> 00:20:37,154
By then, you'll be inside the capsule.

353
00:20:37,909 --> 00:20:40,167
When the prime recovery carrier
arrives,

354
00:20:40,203 --> 00:20:44,118
they'll find you inside the capsule
and take you out of the spacecraft.

355
00:20:45,543 --> 00:20:47,037
You've thought of everything.

356
00:20:47,712 --> 00:20:49,254
I don't know. I hope so.

357
00:20:51,132 --> 00:20:53,837
Of course, you're sure we'll go along,
right?

358
00:20:55,011 --> 00:20:56,292
No, I'm not.

359
00:20:57,055 --> 00:20:58,633
What if we say no?

360
00:20:59,641 --> 00:21:00,637
I don't know.

361
00:21:01,769 --> 00:21:02,848
Don't say no.

362
00:21:03,020 --> 00:21:06,232
When does Allen Funt come running in
and tell us we're on Candid Camera?

363
00:21:06,268 --> 00:21:08,656
Jesus! you think I like this?

364
00:21:08,693 --> 00:21:11,529
You think I really believe I'm standing
here in this craziness

365
00:21:11,566 --> 00:21:13,954
telling you about patching
and tape recordings

366
00:21:13,990 --> 00:21:17,656
and telemetry and an island two
hundred miles from the target zone?

367
00:21:17,870 --> 00:21:20,408
I don't, I don't know what the hell
I'm doing, either!

368
00:21:20,789 --> 00:21:24,574
I just case so Goddamn much,
I think it's worth it.

369
00:21:24,836 --> 00:21:27,790
I'm not even sure of that.
I just think it.

370
00:21:28,256 --> 00:21:29,798
I think I'm gonna throw up.

371
00:21:30,675 --> 00:21:32,239
Well, that'll solve everything.

372
00:21:32,276 --> 00:21:33,767
Well, what's this all gonna solve?

373
00:21:33,804 --> 00:21:36,129
It'll keep something alive
that shouldn't die!

374
00:21:36,348 --> 00:21:40,216
Before you all begin to moralize,
you take a look around.

375
00:21:40,853 --> 00:21:44,305
You look at what we've done and
how much more we can do.

376
00:21:45,233 --> 00:21:47,753
You look at what we've meant
to this country.

377
00:21:47,790 --> 00:21:50,274
Nobody gives a crap about anything
any more.

378
00:21:51,531 --> 00:21:54,076
People close their garages,
and triple lock their doors,

379
00:21:54,112 --> 00:21:56,584
they hide under the beds,
they even, they're even afraid

380
00:21:56,620 --> 00:21:59,749
to turn on their television sets
for fear of what they might find out

381
00:21:59,785 --> 00:22:00,911
in the evening news.

382
00:22:01,459 --> 00:22:03,368
There's nothing more to believe in.

383
00:22:03,628 --> 00:22:06,214
Now, you wanna blow this whole thing
wide open?

384
00:22:06,251 --> 00:22:08,254
God knows what it might do
to everybody.

385
00:22:08,592 --> 00:22:12,179
I'm sorry. I'm so Goddamn sorry.
I just don't know what else to do.

386
00:22:12,215 --> 00:22:15,595
I'm hanging on by my fingernails,
just like everybody else.

387
00:22:16,058 --> 00:22:18,217
Go on, you, you wanna be the ones

388
00:22:18,769 --> 00:22:21,771
who give everyone another reason
to give up?

389
00:22:21,981 --> 00:22:22,977
Go on!

390
00:22:25,485 --> 00:22:27,193
This is really wonderful.

391
00:22:27,988 --> 00:22:29,745
We go along with you

392
00:22:29,782 --> 00:22:33,281
and lie our asses off,
and the world of truth and ideals is...

393
00:22:33,577 --> 00:22:34,609
protected.

394
00:22:35,246 --> 00:22:37,874
But we don't wanna take part in
some giant ripe-off of yours

395
00:22:37,910 --> 00:22:40,502
and some how or other
we're managing to ruin the country.

396
00:22:40,538 --> 00:22:42,730
You're pretty good, Jim.
I'll give you that.

397
00:22:42,767 --> 00:22:44,887
Now, now, now, you're twisting
my words.

398
00:22:44,923 --> 00:22:47,675
- Don't sell yourself short!
- Don't sell the program short!

399
00:22:47,926 --> 00:22:50,714
Don't oversell it. I'm not so sure
that cancelling a flight

400
00:22:51,180 --> 00:22:54,680
or cutting off appropriations
means America folds up.

401
00:22:54,934 --> 00:22:56,936
It's not as simple as that
and you know it!

402
00:22:56,973 --> 00:22:58,016
I don't know it.

403
00:22:58,813 --> 00:23:01,387
If the only way to keep
something alive

404
00:23:02,401 --> 00:23:04,192
is to become everything I hate,

405
00:23:04,945 --> 00:23:07,156
I don't know if it's worth
keeping it alive.

406
00:23:07,192 --> 00:23:09,694
Please, Bru, don't talk like that.

407
00:23:09,825 --> 00:23:13,037
What the hell's the matter with you,
'Please, Bru, don't talk like that?'

408
00:23:13,074 --> 00:23:15,873
I don't think this is right!
All the rest is bullshit!

409
00:23:16,750 --> 00:23:17,829
You have to help!

410
00:23:18,084 --> 00:23:20,754
- What do you mean I have to?
- You have to help!

411
00:23:21,004 --> 00:23:22,428
And what if I don't?

412
00:23:22,464 --> 00:23:25,300
Please, don't put me in a corner.

413
00:23:26,177 --> 00:23:27,457
You're crazy.

414
00:23:28,054 --> 00:23:31,975
You know that? You are crazy! You've
got us in the middle of this nuthouse!

415
00:23:32,011 --> 00:23:33,766
and you don't wanna be put
in a corner?

416
00:23:35,395 --> 00:23:36,426
Your families!

417
00:23:38,815 --> 00:23:41,652
- What about our families?
- Please, you have to help!

418
00:23:41,688 --> 00:23:44,029
- What about our families?
- You have to help!

419
00:23:44,066 --> 00:23:45,995
Shit, this thing is outta my hands!

420
00:23:46,032 --> 00:23:48,284
You think it's all a couple
of looney scientists?

421
00:23:48,321 --> 00:23:49,613
It's not! It's bigger!

422
00:23:50,495 --> 00:23:53,600
There are people out there,
forces out there,

423
00:23:53,637 --> 00:23:56,706
who have a lot to lose!
They are grown-ups!

424
00:23:57,085 --> 00:23:59,421
It's gotten too big!
It's in the hands of grown-ups!

425
00:23:59,458 --> 00:24:00,594
What about our families?

426
00:24:00,631 --> 00:24:04,463
They are flying back from the Cape to
Houston! They are all on the plane!

427
00:24:05,344 --> 00:24:06,803
Naw, you're not serious.

428
00:24:07,388 --> 00:24:11,393
- Please, Bru, don't make me!
- You son-of-a-bitch, tell me!

429
00:24:11,429 --> 00:24:14,596
They're on the plane together!
You want it in writing?

430
00:24:15,772 --> 00:24:18,014
There's a device! It's on the plane!

431
00:24:18,859 --> 00:24:22,530
There's some people! If I don't give
the 'all clear' signal they'll explode it!

432
00:24:22,566 --> 00:24:26,534
Don't you understand?
It doesn't have to be like this!

433
00:24:26,571 --> 00:24:27,945
You have to help!

434
00:24:28,161 --> 00:24:30,617
It's gotten outta control! It's too big!

435
00:24:33,166 --> 00:24:34,412
You wouldn't.

436
00:24:36,211 --> 00:24:37,587
Tell me you wouldn't.

437
00:24:42,009 --> 00:24:43,919
I, I can't tell you that, Bru.

438
00:24:52,396 --> 00:24:53,974
This coffee is horrible.

439
00:24:54,857 --> 00:24:57,526
- It's not that bad.
- It is. It's that bad.

440
00:24:57,860 --> 00:24:59,023
Don't drink it.

441
00:24:59,111 --> 00:25:01,603
I'm always unwrapping things.

