00:25:07,204 --> 00:25:11,125
even the toilet has a paper band on it
with a nice little note from the hotel

445
00:25:11,161 --> 00:25:14,328
saying they put the band on the toilet
for my protection.

446
00:25:15,421 --> 00:25:17,444
I'm afraid that if I stay
in bed too long,

447
00:25:17,480 --> 00:25:19,467
the maid walks in the room
and surround me and

448
00:25:19,504 --> 00:25:21,094
the bread spread with a paper band.

449
00:25:21,130 --> 00:25:21,892
I don't mind.

450
00:25:21,928 --> 00:25:24,603
You wait. After a while you won't
know what city you are in.

451
00:25:24,639 --> 00:25:28,185
I defy anyone to tell me the difference
between the Holiday Inn in Houston

452
00:25:28,221 --> 00:25:31,438
and the Holiday Inn in Cincinnati.
The rooms are the same.

453
00:25:31,475 --> 00:25:33,237
The music in the elevators
is the same,

454
00:25:33,274 --> 00:25:36,360
even the ladies with too much makeup
in the coffee shop are the same.

455
00:25:36,397 --> 00:25:38,822
You never know where you are
until after breakfast,

456
00:25:38,858 --> 00:25:41,110
- when you read the paper.
- I don't mind it.

457
00:25:41,658 --> 00:25:43,624
Well, I don't mind it that much, either.

458
00:25:43,660 --> 00:25:46,872
It's just that I would like it all to be
with someone I care for,

459
00:25:46,908 --> 00:25:48,546
someone I could share it with.

460
00:25:48,582 --> 00:25:51,073
- Bullshit.
- You're so damn cynical.

461
00:25:51,377 --> 00:25:54,422
I'm not cynical. It's just that your act
could use a little polish.

462
00:25:54,458 --> 00:25:56,716
- What do you mean by that?
- Liz Haller, for starter.

463
00:25:56,753 --> 00:25:58,792
It was at the California Primary?

464
00:25:59,010 --> 00:26:03,140
I believe you used the one about both
witnessing to the unfolding of history.

465
00:26:03,176 --> 00:26:05,392
You've got to admit it's better
than soap wrappers.

466
00:26:05,429 --> 00:26:07,765
You think all I wanna do is jump you.

467
00:26:08,104 --> 00:26:09,099
Yes.

468
00:26:09,438 --> 00:26:11,976
You wouldn't know sincerity
if it ran over you.

469
00:26:12,150 --> 00:26:15,069
- Not if you were driving it.
- I'm glad I'm not like you.

470
00:26:15,106 --> 00:26:16,528
I have better legs.

471
00:26:17,322 --> 00:26:18,816
Okay, I give up.

472
00:26:19,950 --> 00:26:23,568
Don't give up so easily,
just change your approach.

473
00:26:23,787 --> 00:26:25,282
What approach would you like?

474
00:26:25,956 --> 00:26:29,252
How about something like, uh,
'I would like to jump you'?

475
00:26:29,288 --> 00:26:30,300
Think that would work?

476
00:26:30,336 --> 00:26:33,339
It has more chance than wanting
to share a life together.

477
00:26:33,376 --> 00:26:35,416
- I would like to jump you.
- Go jump yourself.

478
00:26:43,392 --> 00:26:46,310
I'm sorry that you had to wait outside
the house all day like this.

479
00:26:46,854 --> 00:26:49,725
There is not much that I can say
except that

480
00:26:50,066 --> 00:26:52,355
I'm very excited
and proud.

481
00:26:53,361 --> 00:26:55,160
Everything seems to be going
smoothly.

482
00:26:55,197 --> 00:26:59,361
Dr. Kelloway called to say that Bru
and the crew were in excellent spirits.

483
00:26:59,702 --> 00:27:02,157
How has all this disrupted
your family routine?

484
00:27:02,663 --> 00:27:04,205
- Terrific question.
- Shove it!

485
00:27:04,540 --> 00:27:07,577
Well, the children will continue
to go to school

486
00:27:07,669 --> 00:27:10,586
and we'll try to maintain
a normal existence.

487
00:27:14,384 --> 00:27:16,428
I suppose that's all that I have to say.

488
00:27:16,465 --> 00:27:17,977
Thank you all for coming.

489
00:27:18,013 --> 00:27:21,014
Uh, I just came out to say hello
and go back inside now.

490
00:27:21,475 --> 00:27:23,053
Thank you. Goodbye.

491
00:27:43,499 --> 00:27:44,495
Dr. Bergen?

492
00:27:46,044 --> 00:27:48,338
- Yes, Elliot?
- I wonder if I could talk to you

493
00:27:48,375 --> 00:27:49,963
- for a moment.
- What is it?

494
00:27:50,424 --> 00:27:53,098
Well, there's somethin'...
I have a problem, sir.

495
00:27:53,135 --> 00:27:55,970
- Oh, are you feeling all right?
- Oh, yes, sir. It's the readout.

496
00:27:57,014 --> 00:27:58,354
What about the readout?

497
00:27:58,391 --> 00:28:00,774
Well, I, I just can't figure
something out.

498
00:28:00,810 --> 00:28:03,902
- Well, perhaps I can be of some help.
- Well, I hope so.

499
00:28:03,938 --> 00:28:06,817
See, I ran a check on the transmission,
on my own on the signals.

500
00:28:06,853 --> 00:28:08,323
- On your own?
- Yes, sir.

501
00:28:08,360 --> 00:28:10,659
- I like your dedication.
- The readout...

502
00:28:10,696 --> 00:28:13,824
The television signals are coming in
ahead of the spacecraft signals.

503
00:28:13,861 --> 00:28:15,832
It's like they're closer or something.

504
00:28:15,868 --> 00:28:19,289
Oh, that's not possible. There must be
some malfunction in your equipment.

505
00:28:19,325 --> 00:28:22,709
Well, I don't think so, Dr. Bergen. You
see, I doubled checked that console.

506
00:28:22,745 --> 00:28:25,420
- Which console are you on?
- Thirty-six, sir.

507
00:28:25,457 --> 00:28:26,885
Well, that's the answer.

508
00:28:26,922 --> 00:28:29,472
We've been having problems
with the circuitry on thirty-six.

509
00:28:29,508 --> 00:28:33,030
We've had trouble with it before.
I'll make sure it's repaired and,

510
00:28:33,066 --> 00:28:36,552
thank you for showing me the problem.
You have initiative, I like that.

511
00:29:24,777 --> 00:29:27,035
<i>This is Paul Cunningham.</i>
<i>Capricorn Control.</i>

512
00:29:27,071 --> 00:29:31,618
<i>We are at T-plus one 131 days,</i>
<i>4 hours, 15 minutes, into the flight.</i>

513
00:29:31,654 --> 00:29:32,999
<i>5 minutes. from landing.</i>

