00:31:02,801 --> 00:31:03,714
<i>zero.</i>

552
00:31:03,927 --> 00:31:06,133
<i>Houston, this is Capricorn One.</i>

553
00:31:07,806 --> 00:31:08,969
<i>We have landed.</i>

554
00:31:40,217 --> 00:31:43,253
- Yes?
<i>- Vice President Price on the line.</i>

555
00:31:46,390 --> 00:31:47,386
Hello.

556
00:31:48,601 --> 00:31:50,178
Hello, Mr. Vice President.

557
00:31:51,771 --> 00:31:53,349
Yes, it's wonderful, isn't it?

558
00:31:54,190 --> 00:31:56,183
Proud moment for all Americans.

559
00:31:58,320 --> 00:32:01,107
You can tell the President
that's very gracious of him.

560
00:32:01,323 --> 00:32:03,197
I appreciate it, I really do.

561
00:32:04,827 --> 00:32:05,823
Thank you.

562
00:32:06,287 --> 00:32:08,410
And my very best to your lovely wife.

563
00:32:09,624 --> 00:32:10,537
Yes.

564
00:32:11,376 --> 00:32:12,371
Goodbye.

565
00:32:15,505 --> 00:32:16,703
Asshole.

566
00:32:28,311 --> 00:32:30,522
Dr., I wonder if I can speak
to you for a moment.

567
00:32:30,558 --> 00:32:32,395
Certainly, what seems to be
the problem?

568
00:32:32,565 --> 00:32:34,973
Well, I just can't figure
something out, sir.

569
00:32:35,318 --> 00:32:36,314
What is that?

570
00:32:37,571 --> 00:32:40,538
Well, I'm not exactly sure,
but it's the readout.

571
00:32:40,574 --> 00:32:44,952
I told Dr. Bergen about it a long time
and he said it was in the console.

572
00:32:45,580 --> 00:32:47,122
I'd like you to take a look at it.

573
00:32:47,874 --> 00:32:50,966
- Well, what console are you on?
- Telemetry, sir, thirty-six.

574
00:32:51,002 --> 00:32:55,048
Oh, yes, Dr. Bergen told me about that.
We had that console repaired.

575
00:32:55,085 --> 00:32:56,722
I know, sir, it's just...

576
00:32:56,759 --> 00:32:58,502
I keep on having the same readouts.

577
00:32:59,094 --> 00:33:01,004
Well, what readout?

578
00:33:01,639 --> 00:33:05,393
Well, sir, I ran a program on my own
just to check something

579
00:33:05,429 --> 00:33:07,302
and the readout is different.

580
00:33:08,396 --> 00:33:10,021
You ran your own program?

581
00:33:11,233 --> 00:33:12,312
Yes, sir,

582
00:33:13,777 --> 00:33:15,022
and...

583
00:33:15,529 --> 00:33:17,071
I don't think it's the console.

584
00:33:19,408 --> 00:33:22,161
Well, we'll have it shut down and
I'll see that it's serviced.

585
00:33:22,198 --> 00:33:24,914
Thank you, Elliot, for bringing
the matter to my attention.

586
00:33:28,835 --> 00:33:30,116
You're welcome, sir.

587
00:33:43,226 --> 00:33:45,682
<i>This is Paul Cunningham,</i>
<i>Capricorn Control.</i>

588
00:33:45,896 --> 00:33:48,982
<i>The Flight Director advises that</i>
<i>the LM crew has been given a Go</i>

