00:38:06,639 --> 00:38:09,142
- Eight ball, five dollars a game.
- I don't feel like it.

671
00:38:09,178 --> 00:38:10,649
- 10 dollars.
- I'm serious.

672
00:38:10,685 --> 00:38:13,521
So am I. I'll even let you break.
Can a person be more serious?

673
00:38:13,558 --> 00:38:14,319
You're drunk.

674
00:38:14,356 --> 00:38:16,566
I knew there was a reason
I was feeling this good.

675
00:38:16,603 --> 00:38:18,025
I need a drink.

676
00:38:18,277 --> 00:38:21,322
Underneath that wash and wear shirt,
you have some heart.

677
00:38:21,358 --> 00:38:23,611
It may be sanforized, but it's a heart.

678
00:38:25,535 --> 00:38:26,448
Mike?

679
00:38:38,757 --> 00:38:41,296
- You said I break.
- I musta been drunk.

680
00:38:47,684 --> 00:38:50,305
- Hard day at the office, dear?
- I don't wanna talk about it.

681
00:38:51,021 --> 00:38:53,941
- Did you break your slide rule?
- I'm not really sure.

682
00:38:53,977 --> 00:38:56,031
I ran a check on my own
transmissions signals.

683
00:38:56,068 --> 00:38:58,612
The numbers came up screwy,
so I told Dr. Bergen about it.

684
00:38:58,649 --> 00:39:00,901
It was like he was pissed at me
for running a check.

685
00:39:00,990 --> 00:39:02,914
He said it must be a console
malfunctioning.

686
00:39:02,950 --> 00:39:05,662
So I told Dr. Kelloway about it
and he said the same thing.

687
00:39:05,698 --> 00:39:08,325
Big deal. What did you expect,
a merit badge?

688
00:39:08,362 --> 00:39:10,952
I guess so.
They must know what they're doing.

689
00:39:11,168 --> 00:39:13,837
Those numbers couldn't have been
right anyway. No way.

690
00:39:13,874 --> 00:39:16,090
If you know the numbers
couldn't have been right,

691
00:39:16,126 --> 00:39:17,335
why are you so upset?

692
00:39:17,591 --> 00:39:20,303
It was the way they reacted.
No double check or anything.

693
00:39:20,339 --> 00:39:23,135
They looked at me like I was a kid
and offered me a cookie.

694
00:39:23,172 --> 00:39:25,932
- What were the numbers?
- I have to admit it is ridiculous.

695
00:39:26,226 --> 00:39:27,685
Good, let's play pool.

696
00:39:33,609 --> 00:39:36,070
Those signals couldn't have
come from 300 miles.

697
00:39:36,107 --> 00:39:37,233
Which signals?

698
00:39:38,281 --> 00:39:39,905
The television transmission.

699
00:39:40,450 --> 00:39:43,620
I think I just sobered up. Would you
tell me what you just told me again?

700
00:39:43,656 --> 00:39:45,494
<i>Hey, Caulfield, telephone.</i>

701
00:39:52,296 --> 00:39:53,245
Hello?

702
00:39:54,632 --> 00:39:56,007
yes, this is Caulfield.

703
00:39:57,176 --> 00:39:58,006
What?

704
00:39:59,095 --> 00:40:01,269
I'm sorry, you'll have to speak
more clearly.

705
00:40:01,306 --> 00:40:04,473
I think we have a bad connection
or something. I can't hear you.

706
00:40:05,978 --> 00:40:06,974
Who?

707
00:40:08,689 --> 00:40:10,397
I don't understand what you want.

708
00:40:11,943 --> 00:40:14,242
Look, if you call the assignment desk,

709
00:40:14,278 --> 00:40:16,852
they'll be glad to send someone over
to cover that for you.

710
00:40:17,532 --> 00:40:20,070
Yes, ask for the assignment desk.

711
00:40:20,869 --> 00:40:22,411
Assignment. That's right.

712
00:40:23,205 --> 00:40:24,236
You're welcome.

713
00:40:41,517 --> 00:40:42,715
Anybody hungry?

714
00:40:43,811 --> 00:40:44,925
No.

715
00:40:46,605 --> 00:40:49,013
Oh, the marvels of American
science.

716
00:40:50,443 --> 00:40:53,480
Here we are, millions of miles
from the Earth

717
00:40:54,239 --> 00:40:56,362
and we can still send out for a pizza.

718
00:40:57,409 --> 00:40:58,868
I'm not gonna do it.

719
00:40:59,703 --> 00:41:00,866
Not gonna do what?

720
00:41:01,163 --> 00:41:03,421
Tomorrow, I'm not gonna sit
in this thing

721
00:41:03,457 --> 00:41:06,162
and talk to my wife and tell her
everything is going fine.

722
00:41:06,252 --> 00:41:07,877
I'm not gonna do it.

723
00:41:10,799 --> 00:41:11,878
I tried.

724
00:41:13,969 --> 00:41:16,886
I got two little kids with big bright eyes.

725
00:41:17,890 --> 00:41:21,176
And I used to tell them their daddy
was gonna make them proud of him

726
00:41:22,311 --> 00:41:24,019
like he was of them.

727
00:41:24,730 --> 00:41:26,355
And now I gotta go home,

728
00:41:26,774 --> 00:41:29,348
I gotta kiss them and
gotta look in their eyes

729
00:41:29,986 --> 00:41:31,813
and tell them I really did this?

730
00:41:34,867 --> 00:41:38,532
I don't know. Maybe that's better that
telling them I really didn't do it.

731
00:41:40,790 --> 00:41:43,079
I wish I knew what was right.
I really don't.

732
00:41:43,292 --> 00:41:46,709
We've been sitting around here for
months, telling their lies for them.

733
00:41:48,715 --> 00:41:50,755
And I don't wanna do it any more.

734
00:41:51,927 --> 00:41:55,222
<i>Okay, so we go and blow the whole</i>
<i>thing tomorrow, on national TV,</i>

735
00:41:55,259 --> 00:41:56,253
<i>then what have we done?</i>

736
00:41:56,473 --> 00:42:00,057
- We'd screw up a lotta people's dinner.
- We've already screwed ourselves.

737
00:42:00,269 --> 00:42:03,153
Okay, so what do we accomplish
by screwing everybody else?

738
00:42:03,189 --> 00:42:06,523
He's got a point there, you know.
We went along with this for you.

739
00:42:07,194 --> 00:42:08,688
You and our families.

740
00:42:09,529 --> 00:42:12,863
Now you wanna go out in
some terrific blaze of glory?

741
00:42:13,742 --> 00:42:15,700
And we get pulverized in the process?

742
00:42:18,998 --> 00:42:20,327
And our families?

743
00:42:25,088 --> 00:42:27,247
- What about our families?
- I know!

744
00:42:34,557 --> 00:42:35,553
I know.

745
00:42:36,726 --> 00:42:37,722
<i>Shit!</i>

746
00:42:38,019 --> 00:42:40,980
<i>That's the best thing I've heard</i>
<i>anybody say in three weeks.</i>

747
00:42:41,017 --> 00:42:42,691
<i>- What's the best thing?</i>
<i>- Shit.</i>

748
00:42:42,727 --> 00:42:44,401
<i>I just don't think I can do it.</i>

749
00:42:44,437 --> 00:42:45,860
Get me Dr. Kelloway.

750
00:42:46,153 --> 00:42:48,656
Why, all of a sudden,
are we standing up for the bad guys

751
00:42:48,692 --> 00:42:51,027
and you're on the side
of truth and justice?

752
00:42:51,063 --> 00:42:53,362
We may have a problem with
Brubaker tomorrow.

753
00:42:53,953 --> 00:42:57,038
- I wish I had the words.
- Damn the words, Bru!

754
00:42:59,125 --> 00:43:01,332
These people... they're capable
of anything.

755
00:43:01,711 --> 00:43:03,621
And we got our families out there.

756
00:43:04,089 --> 00:43:07,090
Now, we're in this thing and I think
we're in too deep to stop now.

757
00:43:07,676 --> 00:43:09,586
No one of us is gonna decide.

758
00:43:11,055 --> 00:43:12,549
It's got to be all of us.

759
00:43:16,686 --> 00:43:19,898
Operator, I'm trying a number now
for over an hour and it's busy.

760
00:43:19,935 --> 00:43:22,389
Would you kindly check to see
if it's out of order?

761
00:43:23,485 --> 00:43:25,277
I know you don't do that.

762
00:43:25,613 --> 00:43:27,107
Yes, it's an emergency.

763
00:43:28,115 --> 00:43:31,698
Thank you. 8733657.

764
00:43:32,495 --> 00:43:35,829
No, 3657, Mr. Elliot Whitter.

765
00:43:42,631 --> 00:43:43,710
Out of order?

766
00:43:44,633 --> 00:43:46,044
Thank you very much, operator.

767
00:43:48,971 --> 00:43:52,329
<i>This is Paul Cunningham,</i>
<i>Capricorn Control.</i>

768
00:43:52,366 --> 00:43:55,230
<i>We are a T-plus 223 days,</i>
<i>6 hours, 32 minutes.</i>

769
00:43:55,267 --> 00:43:58,095
<i>All systems are go.</i>
<i>All lights are green.</i>

770
00:43:58,232 --> 00:44:01,235
<i>We are awaiting the start of the</i>
<i>final television transmissions</i>

771
00:44:01,271 --> 00:44:03,785
<i>from the Command Module</i>
<i>on its return to Earth.</i>

772
00:44:03,821 --> 00:44:07,902
<i>This is specifically a conversation</i>
<i>between the crew and their wives.</i>

